Which numbers do you try for the combination lock?\n\n[[1, 14, 17]]\n[[2, 15, 18]]\n[[3, 16, 18]]\n[[4, 17, 18]]
You unlock the door with the key you found and crack it slightly. As you peer through the crack you see a long, dark hallway. At the end of the hallway is a closed door. This is where the voices are. You are no coward, but you feel yourself tremble with fear, knowing that Death Eaters and the Dark Lord wait on the other side of the door. \n\n"There's only one way out," you tell yourself, grabbing the doorknob and flinging the door open, ready to [[fight|fight and die]].
You put your ear to the door, trying to make out the words being said. Unfortunately, they are too far away. You may not be able to understand the words, but you can hear the excitement in everyone's voices. You have to [[open the door]] as it is the only way out.

You decipher the code and see the title Magick Moste Evile. You look around the room and see it sitting on a bookshelf leaned against the wall. You leaf through the book and find a [[key]]!\n[img[key 2]]
The Dark Lord lies before you, vanquished. Seeing this, the Death Eaters disappear from the room, disapparating to whichever dark corner of the wizarding world they came from. Without a powerful leader they are nothing. The door out of the building is still locked and won't open. You make your way back to the [[vanishing cabinet]].
<<set $hp to 10>>\n<<set $dlhp to 10>>\nThe Dark Lord readies his wand, prepared to strike you down. Quickly recalling your duelling lessons, you hold up your wand to beam a spell at the [[Dark Lord]].
You survey the library's thousands of shelves, noting the floating candelabras illuminuating the library in an eerie fashion. As you turn to tug at the handle one last time, a note appears suddenly scrawled across the door. \n[img[stuck door message]]\n"Is someone playing a prank on me?" you think as you [[turn]] to face the library once again.\n
You browse the 540 section for the Basic to Advanced Potions book and find it right where it should be in Chemistry. You pull the book off the shelf, consulting the glossary and turning to the correct page. You say the missing ingredient outloud, "[[lacewing flies]]."
The Dark Lord stares at you, expecting a response. You choke out "What do you mean?" One of the Death Eaters responds, "We have been biding our time since Lord Voldemort was defeated. We have been waiting for a new a master. He has arrived and you will be his first victim." Your mouth opens in disbelief as you realize this was indeed a trap all along. \n\nThe Dark Lord asks you "Do you [[fight]] bravely or run like a [[coward]]?"

Escape from Hogwarts Library
You sneak through the cracked door and make your way down the dark hallway. The floor creaks slightly under the weight of your feet as you try to be as quiet as possible. When you reach the other door you put your ear to it and hear the worst thing imaginable "The Dark Lord has [[returned]]!"
You feel your body fly through the darkness and suddenly you reappear in another cabinet. It dawns on you that you just used a vanishing cabinet and have now been transported to the other cabinet's location. While you sort out your thoughts, you hear several muffled voices speaking in the distance. It almost sounds like someone is having a [[meeting|dark room]].

You re-enter the vanishing cabinet and are transported back to Hogwarts. As you walk out of the secret room you discovered in the library, you see sunlight starting to stream through the windows. Will anyone believe what [[happened]]?
You browse the 530 section for the Basic to Advanced Potions book and find nothing.\n[[Try another section|class]].
As your eyes become accustomed to the darkness, you look around the room. It is old and dusty, with the aroma of decay hanging in the air. Taking care to be quiet, you try the doorknob of the room and it is locked. You grab the wand you found in the library commanding "alohomora," but the door won't budge. It looks like it needs an actual key to unlock it from the [[inside|cipher]].\n[img[doorknob]]
After you say the missing ingredient outloud, the book shelf in front of you shakes violently and then slowly swings open revealing a [[hidden room]]. \n[img[hidden door]]
As you tug on the lock it unlocks in your hand. The cabinet opens. You note that is human sized and a thought crosses your mind. "Do I need to get in the cabinet?" Of course you do. You take a deep breath, open the door and step into the [[darkness|meeting]].
As you examine the lock, another note appears. \n[img[cipher message]]\nYou attempt to unscramble the letters in your mind but it doesn't make sense. Perhaps this is some kind of secret code.\nWhat does the code say?\n\n[[Magick About Counter Curses]]\n[[Magick After Jinxs]]\n[[Magick Moste Evile]]\n[[Magick After Evile]]
You grab the key and walk over to the door. The muffled voices grow louder. Do you wait and [[listen more]] or immediately [[open the door]]?
Although it is becoming near closing time, you return to your studying, relying on Madam Pince to let you know it's time to close. You continue reading, feeling your eyes become heavy and start to close, then darkness. \nThe crashing of a closing door [[jolts you awake.]]

As the door flies open you peer into the room. Everyone is looking at you. No one appears surprised by your presence. It's almost as if they were waiting for you. The sinking feeling in your stomach starts to gnaw at your senses. What if they were waiting for you? Was this an elaborate [[trap]]?

You wake up with your forehead on your book. You ask yourself "Did I fall asleep? Did someone cast a sleeping spell on me? What happened? Where is everybody?" As these questions swirl through your head, you make your way to the front door of the library, only to find it locked from the outside. You are [[stuck]]. \n[img[library door]]
There's no shame in running. You spot another door that must lead to the front of the house. You dash for the door but with the flick of a wand another Death Eater closes the door and locks it before you can even get there. You must [[fight]].

As soon as you face the library a briefcase appears at your feet. You pick it up, noting a combination lock securing the briefcase. You try the only unlocking spell you know, which doesn't work of course. The lock must be opened manually. As you turn the briefcase over, you see another note scrawled across it. \n[img[briefcase message]]\nWere the rumors true? Were the Death Eaters back? You needed to [[escape]]!
You enter the numbers 4, 17, 18 with no success. Try another [[combination|escape]].

"Our first victim has arrived." You hear these words and look to the front of the large room. Surrounded by 20-30 Death Eaters is a tall and imposing man. His skin is pale, but he doesn't have the features of a snake. Instead, his nose portrudes into a snout, with long hair and fangs. His hands are human-like, but have long sharp nails portruding from each finger. Draped over his powerful body is a long dark cloak. This may not be Lord Voldemort, but it is most certainly [[the Dark Lord]].
